REQUIREMENTS:
- labels: exactly one entry per destination above, {"to": N, "label": "..."}.
- A label is the player's voice: a concrete present-tense action, no outcomes
  revealed. No meta-language — "continue", "go to the next scene" are failures;
  even a single onward choice deserves a diegetic line.
{% if dests | length > 1 %}- Labels leaving this passage must differ from one another.
{% endif %}- Match the tone. Never mention flags, dilemmas, or structure in a label.
